CodeList.Name: Reason CS/LV Lead Not Implanted

Description.TranslatedText: The reason that a Coronary Sinus Access or Left Ventricular (CS/LV) lead was not implanted.

EnumeratedItem.CodedValue: COULD NOT OBTAIN ACCEPTABLE PACING THRESHOLDS
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCDefinition: The coronary sinus/left ventricular lead was not implanted because the operator was unable to obtain acceptable pacing thresholds.
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:PreferredTerm: Unable to Obtain Acceptable Pacing Thresholds

EnumeratedItem.CodedValue: LEAD POSITION RESULTS IN UNDESIRABLE STIMULATION OF THE DIAPHRAGM
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCDefinition: The coronary sinus/left ventricular lead was not implanted because the lead position resulted in undesirable stimulation of the diaphragm.
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:PreferredTerm: Cardiac Lead Position Results in Undesirable Stimulation of Diaphragm

EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCDefinition: The coronary sinus/left ventricular lead was not implanted because a lead had been previously implanted.

EnumeratedItem.CodedValue: UNABLE TO OBTAIN SATISFACTORY CORONARY SINUS ACCESS
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCDefinition: The coronary sinus/left ventricular lead was not implanted because the operator was unable to obtain satisfactory coronary sinus access.
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:PreferredTerm: Unable to Obtain Satisfactory Coronary Sinus Access

EnumeratedItem.CodedValue: UNABLE TO OBTAIN SATISFACTORY VASCULAR ACCESS
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCDefinition: The coronary sinus/left ventricular lead was not implanted because the operator was unable to obtain satisfactory vascular access.
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:PreferredTerm: Unable to Obtain Satisfactory Vascular Access

EnumeratedItem.CodedValue: UNABLE TO POSITION LEAD DUE TO CORONARY SINUS DISSECTION
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCDefinition: The coronary sinus/left ventricular lead was not implanted because the coronary sinus was dissected.
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:PreferredTerm: Unable to Position Lead Due to Coronary Sinus Dissection

EnumeratedItem.CodedValue: UNABLE TO POSITION LEAD IN TRIBUTARY VEIN OF CORONARY SINUS
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:CDISCDefinition: The coronary sinus/left ventricular lead was not implanted because the operator was unable to position the lead in the tributary vein of the coronary sinus.
EnumeratedItem.nciodm:PreferredTerm: Unable to Position Lead In tributary Vein of Coronary Sinus

CodeList.nciodm:PreferredTerm: CDISC SDTM Reason Coronary Sinus Access or Left Ventricular Lead Not Implanted Terminology
